Note : Due to the length of some processes, we have made the notification setting using the win10toast library for windows to inform the computer. please make the necessary operations If your computer's operating system is not Windows 10.

You can access the presentation of the project from the link. https://prezi.com/view/YKUlBDLQSaheIAyLOwzh/

Plan¶

  1. Defining the data set
  2. Obtaining basic information about the data set
  3. Basic operations on data set (tokenization, stemming, lemmatization, pos, chunking, ...)
  4. Mathematical Operations and Simple Feature Extraction
  5. Wordcloud
  6. Comparing Algorithms (Count Vector, Word Level/Char Level/N-Gram TF-IDF)
  7. Comparing ML Algorithms
  8. Determining the most successful ML algorithm and training with it
  9. After the training, processing on the test data
  10. Finding the most successful model for Toxicty prediction (Decision Trees vs Neural Network)
  11. Using the most successful method for toxicity estimation

In [95]:
"Get the top n values tfidf overlap and rotate with the corresponding attribute name.."
    
def top_tfidf_feats(row, features, top_n=30):
    topn_ids = np.argsort(row)[::-1][:top_n]
    top_feats = [(features[i], row[i]) for i in topn_ids]
    df = pd.DataFrame(top_feats)
    df.columns = ['feature', 'tfidf']
    return df

"On average, return the most important of the properties among documents in rows specified in Grp_ids directories."

def top_mean_feats(Xtr, features, grp_ids, min_tfidf=0.1, top_n=30):
    D = Xtr[grp_ids].toarray()
    D[D < min_tfidf] = 0
    tfidf_means = np.mean(D, axis=0)
    return top_tfidf_feats(tfidf_means, features, top_n)


# modified for multilabel milticlass
"Returns a list of dfs where each df contains the properties of top_n and the average tfidf value calculated between documents with the same class tag."
def top_feats_by_class(Xtr, features, min_tfidf=0.1, top_n=30):
    dfs = []
    columns_ = train_tags.columns
    for col in columns_:
        ids = train_tags.index[train_tags[col] == 1]
        feats_df = top_mean_feats(Xtr, features, ids, min_tfidf=min_tfidf, top_n=top_n)
        feats_df.label = classes
        dfs.append(feats_df)
    return dfs

In [158]:
#uppercase / lowercase transformation
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x.lower() for x in x.split()))
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x.lower() for x in x.split()))
#removing punctuation marks
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].str.replace('[^\w\s]','')
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].str.replace('[^\w\s]','')
#removal of numbers
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].str.replace('\d','')
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].str.replace('\d','')
#stopwords
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x for x in x.split() if x not in sw))
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x for x in x.split() if x not in sw))
#deleting rare words
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x for x in x.split() if x not in del_))
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x for x in x.split() if x not in del_))
#lemmin
train_df["comment_text"] = train_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join([Word(word).lemmatize() for word in x.split()])) 
test_df["comment_text"] = test_df["comment_text"].apply(lambda x: " ".join([Word(word).lemmatize() for word in x.split()]))
